      • Serialized Fields

        • dManager

          DisplayManager dManager
          dManager and db hold references to DisplayManager and Database, respectively, to ensure the correct instances of those objects are being manipulated. records is the main JList widget, which is closely related to its listModel its container, scrollPane. strMonths, strDays, and strYears are arrays for use in the combo boxes. The following are the other necessary GUI widgets: btnAdd, btnCalc, btnDelete, boxDays, boxMonths, boxYears, lblOunces, lblPrice, lblSilver, txtOunces, txtPrice, and txtSilver. didDisplayRecords is a boolean variable used for the JUnit assert statement.
